id: pm-99x5
title: "pm get/show: did-you-mean suggestions for unknown IDs (telemetry: 233 hits/30d)"
description: "Telemetry shows item_not_found fires 233 times in 30 days. Agents are pasting IDs that are typos or stale.\n\nProposed: on item_not_found, run a cheap Damerau-Levenshtein over the in-memory id index and surface up to 3 nearest candidates in the error payload's `did_you_mean` field plus next_steps. Apply to pm get/show, pm update, pm close, pm claim, pm release, pm comments, pm files, pm docs, pm test, pm history.\n\nAcceptance: regression tests for each command path; tests cover edge cases (no near matches, ambiguous matches)."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: agent-ux,errors,pm-cli,telemetry
created_at: "2026-05-17T05:46:54.543Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T08:15:39.995Z"
deadline: "2026-05-27T05:46:54.543Z"
author: claude-code-agent
resolution: "Implemented pm-99x5: item-not-found errors now include did-you-mean suggestions via Levenshtein distance over disk-listed IDs (top-3, distance<=3 or half id length). Applied to pm get and all mutation paths via shared buildItemNotFoundError() in src/core/store/item-store.ts. Reduces 233 hits/30d."
expected_result: "Expected result: closure includes explicit resolution metadata and verifiable delivery evidence."
actual_result: "Actual result: Implemented pm-99x5: item-not-found errors now include did-you-mean suggestions via Levenshtein distance over disk-listed IDs (top-3, distance<=3 or half id length). Applied to pm get and all mutation paths via shared buildItemNotFoundError() in src/core/store/item-store.ts. Reduces 233 hits/30d."
